        "content": "<p>surajk-m opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13399\">PR #13399</a> from <code>surajk-m:fix/issue-13076</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Closes #13076.</p>\n<p>Sub-word <code>atomic_rmw</code> (i8/i16) loops on riscv64 emitted a second <code>lr.w.aqrl</code> before the merge step, which cancelled the reservation from the first LR. The <code>sc.w.aqrl</code> was then paired only with the reload, breaking atomicity.</p>\n<p><strong>Fix:</strong> replace the second LR with <code>gen_move</code> to stash the already loaded word into <code>spilltmp2</code>, so the loop keeps a single LR/SC pair.</p>\n<p>Affected ops: <code>add</code>, <code>sub</code>, <code>and</code>, <code>or</code>, <code>xor</code>, <code>nand</code>, <code>xchg</code>, <code>umin</code>, <code>umax</code>, <code>smin</code>, <code>smax</code> for <code>i8</code>/<code>i16</code>. </p>\n<p>A dedicated filetest (<code>issue-13076.clif</code>) pins the single LR/SC shape for each affected op.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 595541515,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1778974294
